Section 1:
1 L.D. 719
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 CRIMINAL JUSTICE AND PUBLIC SAFETY
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 458, L.D. 719, “An Act to Amend the
10 Share of State Funding for the County Jail Operations Fund”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'Resolve, to Direct the County Corrections Professional Standards Council to
13 Examine Funding of and Compliance by County and Regional Jails'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
15 'Sec. 1. County Corrections Professional Standards Council report.
16 Resolved: That the County Corrections Professional Standards Council, as established in
17 the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 5, section 12004-G, subsection 6-D, referred to in this
18 resolve as "the council," shall review information regarding the share of state funding for
19 the County Jail Operations Fund established in Title 34-A, section 1210-E and county and
20 regional jail compliance with certain statutory requirements or rules. In conducting this
21 review, the council shall:
22 1. Review the status of county and regional jail compliance with audit requirements
23 pursuant to Title 30-A, section 1662, subsection 2 and examine ways to incentivize
24 compliance with these requirements;
25 2. Review the status of county and regional jail reporting to the Department of
26 Corrections for expenses associated with operating county and regional jails pursuant to
27 Title 34-A, section 1208-B, subsection 5 and examine ways to incentivize compliance with
28 these requirements;
29 3. Review any unfunded mandates related to county and regional jails;
30 4. Examine improvements to the operations of the council; and
31 5. Examine future needs for state support for county and regional jail operations.
32 Sec. 2. Report. Resolved: That, no later than January 15, 2026, the council shall
33 submit a report based on the study under section 1, including any recommendations and
34 suggested legislation, to the Joint Standing Committee on Criminal Justice and Public
Page 1 - 132LR0852(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 458, L.D. 719
315 Safety. The committee may submit legislation based on the report to the Second Regular
326 Session of the 132nd Legislature.'
3 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
4 number to read consecutively.
5 SUMMARY
66 This amendment replaces the bill with a resolve. The amendment directs the County
77 Corrections Professional Standards Council to examine county and regional jail
88 compliance with financial reporting requirements and examine state funding for county and
99 regional jails, including reviewing the status of county and regional jail compliance with
1100 financial auditing requirements, reviewing the status of county and regional jail reporting
1111 of operating expenses to the Department of Corrections, reviewing any unfunded mandates
1122 related to county and regional jails, examining improvements to the operations of the
1133 County Corrections Professional Standards Council and examining future needs for state
1144 support for county and regional jail operations.
15 This amendment requires that the County Corrections Professional Standards Council
16 submit a report by January 15, 2026 to the Joint Standing Committee on Criminal Justice
17 and Public Safety, which may submit legislation to the Second Regular Session of the
18 132nd Legislature.
1199 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2200 (See attached)
